    content: `## Moringa vs Spinach vs Kale: The Data\n\n### Nutritional Comparison (per 100g dry weight)\n\n| Nutrient | Moringa Powder | Spinach | Kale |\n|----------|--------------|---------|------|\n| Protein (g) | 27.1 | 2.9 | 4.3 |\n| Iron (mg) | 28.2 | 2.7 | 1.5 |\n| Calcium (mg) | 2003 | 99 | 135 |\n| Vitamin A (IU) | 16333 | 9377 | 9990 |\n| Vitamin C (mg) | 220 | 28.1 | 120 |\n| Vitamin E (mg) | 113 | 2.03 | 1.54 |\n| Magnesium (mg) | 147 | 79 | 34 |\n| Potassium (mg) | 1324 | 558 | 447 |\n| Fibre (g) | 19.2 | 2.2 | 3.6 |\n| ORAC Value | 157,000 | 1,513 | 4,812 |\n\n### Score Card: Moringa wins 11/14 parameters\n\n**Moringa Wins**: Protein, Iron, Calcium, Vitamin A, Vitamin C, Vitamin E, Magnesium, Potassium, Fibre, ORAC, Amino Acid Profile\n\n**Kale Wins**: Vitamin K, Glucosinolates\n\n**Spinach Wins**: Lower calorie density\n\n## Why Moringa is the Superfood Champion\n\nPowder form means extraordinary concentration. One teaspoon of Moringa Powder (5g) provides:\n- **900% of RDA Vitamin A**\n- **60% of RDA Vitamin C**\n- **190% of RDA Iron** (for women)\n- **20% of RDA Calcium**\n\nNo other single plant powder matches this density.\n\n## For Retailers and Affiliates\n\nThe comparison story is your sales story. Use this data in:\n- Product descriptions\n- Social media posts\n- YouTube video scripts\n- Email marketing\n- Product packaging claims\n\n*Use our comparison infographic (available to registered affiliates) to boost your conversion rate.*`
