    readTime: "5 min",
    author: "Sachin Shinde",
    excerpt: "Poor storage can destroy Moringa's nutritional value within weeks. Learn professional storage practices from the source.",
    thumbnail: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=600&q=80",
    seoTitle: "How to Store Moringa Powder: Keep It Fresh for 24 Months",
    seoDesc: "Professional moringa powder storage guidelines. Temperature, moisture, light exposure, and container types that preserve nutritional value.",
    keywords: ["moringa powder storage", "how to store moringa", "moringa shelf life"],
    content: `## Proper Storage for Moringa Powder\n\n### The 4 Enemies of Moringa Quality\n1. **Moisture** — causes clumping, mold growth, aflatoxin\n2. **Heat** — degrades Vitamin C, chlorophyll, and enzymes\n3. **Light** — UV exposure oxidizes polyphenols and carotenoids\n4. **Oxygen** — oxidizes fatty acids, reduces antioxidant capacity\n\n### Storage Requirements by Format\n\n| Format | Temp | Humidity | Container | Shelf Life |\n|--------|------|---------|-----------|----------|\n| Sealed Factory Bag | <25°C | <50% RH | Nitrogen-flushed | 24-36 months |\n| Opened Bag | <20°C | <40% RH | Airtight glass jar | 6-8 months |\n| Retail Pack | Room temp | Normal | Keep sealed | 12-18 months |\n| Capsules | <25°C | Normal | Blister pack | 24 months |\n\n### For Bulk Exporters\n\n- **Warehouse**: Temperature 15-25°C, humidity <60% RH\n- **Pallets**: Off-floor (10cm minimum), away from walls\n- **No direct sunlight**: Blackout curtains or dark warehouse sections\n- **Pest control**: HACCP-certified facility with regular rodent/insect audits\n- **FIFO rotation**: First In, First Out — mandatory\n\n### Container Selection Guide\n\n**Best**: Dark glass jar with silica gel desiccant\n**Good**: Opaque HDPE container with tight lid\n**Acceptable**: Food-grade zip-lock pouch with all air pressed out\n**Avoid**: Clear containers, damp cupboards, near stove or oven\n\n### Freshness Test\n- Color: Still vibrant green? → Good\n- Smell: Fresh, green, slightly earthy → Good\n- Clumping: Slight is OK if color preserved\n- Taste: Bitter/earthy = fine; musty = discard\n\n### For Retailers: Consumer Storage Instructions\nPrint on label: "Store in a cool, dry place away from direct sunlight. Refrigerate after opening for maximum freshness. Consume within 6 months of opening."\n\n*All Avani Agro Foods Moringa Powder is packed in nitrogen-flushed, moisture-barrier bags to guarantee maximum freshness on arrival.*`
