    keywords: ["export moringa powder india", "moringa export registration", "IEC registration india"],
    content: `## Step-by-Step Guide: Exporting Moringa Powder from India\n\n### Step 1: Business Registration\n- **Proprietorship/Partnership/Pvt Ltd** — any works\n- Register with **MSME** (Udyam Registration) for benefits\n- Open a **current bank account** in business name\n\n### Step 2: Get IEC (Import Export Code)\n- Apply at **DGFT** (dgft.gov.in)\n- Cost: ₹500 (government fee)\n- Time: 2-3 working days (online)\n- Required documents: PAN, Aadhaar, Bank certificate, Address proof\n\n### Step 3: FSSAI Registration\n- Mandatory for food products\n- State License for <₹12 Cr turnover\n- Central License for exports\n- Time: 30-60 days\n- Cost: ₹2,000-₹7,500 depending on scale\n\n### Step 4: APEDA Registration\n- Agricultural and Processed Food Products Export Development Authority\n- Website: apeda.gov.in\n- Cost: ₹5,900 (one-time)\n- Required for: Moringa Powder export certification and RCMC\n\n### Step 5: GST Registration\n- Mandatory for exports\n- Zero-rated supply under GST (export gets LUT/Refund)\n- Apply at gstin.gov.in\n\n### Step 6: Quality Testing\nGet your product tested at:\n- **NABL-accredited labs** (FSSAI approved)\n- Minimum tests: Microbiological, Heavy Metals, Pesticides, Nutritional profile\n- Cost: ₹3,000-₹15,000 per batch\n- Certificates: CoA (Certificate of Analysis)\n\n### Step 7: Packaging Compliance\n- **Label must include**: Product name, Weight, Ingredients, Storage, Batch No., Mfg date, Best before, Exporter address, Importer address (if pre-labeled)\n- **Language**: English + destination country language if required\n- **Organic claim**: Requires APEDA/NPOP certification\n\n### Step 8: Find Buyers\n- **APEDA Buyer-Seller Meets**\n- **IndiaMART, Alibaba, ExportHub** (B2B platforms)\n- **LinkedIn** (export groups)\n- **Digital marketing** (website + WhatsApp + Instagram)\n- **Trade fairs**: Anuga, SIAL, FoodEx Japan, Saudi Foodex\n\n### Step 9: Shipping and Logistics\n- **Agent**: Appoint a Custom House Agent (CHA)\n- **Terms**: FOB Nhava Sheva / FOB Chennai / CIF destination\n- **Documents required**: Commercial Invoice, Packing List, Bill of Lading, Certificate of Origin, Phytosanitary, CoA, FSSAI cert\n\n### Step 10: Receive Payment\n- **LC (Letter of Credit)**: Safest for new buyers\n- **TT (Wire Transfer)**: 30-50% advance, balance before shipping\n- **DP (Documents against Payment)**: Medium risk\n- Bank must be informed for FEMA compliance\n\n## HS Codes for Moringa Export\n- Moringa Powder: **HS 0712.90.90**\n- Red Onion Powder: **HS 0712.20.00**\n- Moringa Oil: **HS 1515.90.90**\n\n*Avani Agro Foods operates as an exporter from Latur, Maharashtra. Contact for collaboration on co-export, sourcing, or trading.*`
