    excerpt: "Complete checklist of all export documents needed for Moringa Powder — from proforma invoice to phytosanitary certificate.",
    thumbnail: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1454165804606-c3d57bc86b40?w=600&q=80",
    seoTitle: "Moringa Powder Export Documentation Checklist | Complete Guide",
    seoDesc: "Complete list of documents required for moringa powder export from India. Proforma invoice, phytosanitary, CoA, SSL, and customs documents explained.",
    keywords: ["moringa export documents", "food export documentation india", "phytosanitary certificate moringa"],
    content: `## Complete Export Document Checklist\n\n### Pre-Shipment Documents\n1. **Proforma Invoice (PI)** — Issued to buyer before shipment; includes quantity, price, terms\n2. **Purchase Order (PO)** — Buyer's formal order document\n3. **Contract of Sale** — Signed agreement with T&C\n\n### Shipment Documents\n4. **Commercial Invoice** — Final invoice; quantity, unit price, total value, HS code\n5. **Packing List** — Detailed list of cartons, weights, dimensions\n6. **Bill of Lading (BL)** — Transport document issued by shipping line\n7. **Airway Bill (AWB)** — For air shipments\n\n### Quality & Regulatory Documents\n8. **Certificate of Analysis (CoA)** — Lab test results (microbiological, heavy metals, pesticides, nutritional)\n9. **Phytosanitary Certificate** — Issued by Plant Quarantine Authority (prevents pests)\n10. **Health Certificate** — For food-grade products (FSSAI/Export Inspection Council)\n11. **Free Sale Certificate** — Confirms product is freely sold in India (EIC)\n12. **Non-GMO Certificate** — Required for EU, Japan, South Korea\n\n### Trade Compliance Documents\n13. **Certificate of Origin (CoO)** — Issued by FIEO/ITPO/Chamber of Commerce\n14. **GST LUT (Letter of Undertaking)** — Zero-rated export without GST payment\n15. **Shipping Bill** — Customs document for export declaration (ICEGATE portal)\n16. **EP Copy (Exchange Control)** — For bank to receive foreign currency\n\n### Special Documents\n17. **APEDA Certificate** — For APEDA-listed products\n18. **USDA Organic Certificate** — For organic claims in USA\n19. **EU Organic Certificate** — For organic claims in EU\n20. **Halal Certificate** — For GCC countries (FIEO accredited body)\n\n## Cost Estimate for Documentation\n| Document | Authority | Cost |\n|---------|----------|------|\n| Phytosanitary | Plant Quarantine | ₹500-1,500 |\n| Health Certificate | EIC | ₹2,000-4,000 |\n| CoO | Chamber/FIEO | ₹200-500 |\n| CoA (Lab test) | NABL Lab | ₹5,000-15,000 |\n| Free Sale | EIC | ₹3,000-8,000 |\n\n## Common Rejection Reasons\n- Heavy metal exceedance (Lead, Arsenic)\n- Aflatoxin presence\n- Salmonella found\n- Incorrect HS code\n- Missing phytosanitary certificate\n- Improper labeling\n\n*Avani Agro Foods provides complete documentation support for all shipments. Contact us for assistance.*`
