    content: `## Moringa Powder Pricing Analysis 2026\n\n### Indian FOB Prices (Nhava Sheva / Chennai)\n| Grade | Moisture | Price Range (USD/kg) |\n|-------|----------|--------------------|\n| Standard (Non-Organic) | <7% | 2.50 - 4.50 |\n| Premium (Non-Organic) | <5% | 4.00 - 7.00 |\n| Organic Certified | <5% | 7.00 - 14.00 |\n| Ultra-Premium (Freeze-dried) | <4% | 15.00 - 25.00 |\n\n### CIF Prices at Destination\n| Destination | CIF Price Range |\n|-------------|----------------|\n| USA (Los Angeles) | USD 8-18/kg |\n| Germany (Hamburg) | EUR 7-15/kg |\n| UAE (Dubai) | USD 5-12/kg |\n| UK (Felixstowe) | GBP 6-14/kg |\n| Japan (Tokyo) | JPY 1,500-3,500/kg |\n| Australia (Sydney) | AUD 10-24/kg |\n\n### Organic Premium\nOrganic Moringa Powder commands **40-80% premium** over conventional.\n\nBreakdown:\n- Conventional: $3.50 FOB → $10-12 retail\n- Organic: $9.00 FOB → $22-35 retail\n\n### Price Drivers in 2026\n1. **Monsoon quality**: Maharashtra, TN, AP crop quality\n2. **USD/INR rate**: INR depreciation improves export competitiveness\n3. **EU Greendeal demand**: Organic mandate increasing organic demand\n4. **Competition**: Ghana, West Africa entering moringa exports at lower prices\n\n### Margin Analysis for Small Exporters\n\nExample: 1 MT Standard Moringa Powder\n- India Farm Gate: ₹150-200/kg (₹1.5-2 Lakh/MT)\n- Processing Cost: ₹30-50/kg\n- Testing + Certification: ₹15-25/kg/batch\n- Packaging + Logistics to Port: ₹20-30/kg\n- **Total Cost**: ₹215-305/kg (~USD 2.50-3.60)\n- **FOB Selling Price**: USD 3.50-5.00/kg\n- **Margin**: 15-45% gross\n\n### 2026-2027 Price Forecast\nGlobal moringa market growing at 9.5% CAGR. Organic premium growing. Supply from India is premium — Ghana undercutting on price but losing on quality.\n\n**Recommendation**: Position as premium certified Indian Moringa, not compete on price.\n\n*Avani Agro Foods: Get a custom quote based on volumes, destination, and quality grade.*`
