    keywords: ["FSSAI registration export", "food export license india", "FSSAI central license"],
    content: `## FSSAI for Food Exporters: Complete Guide\n\n### Types of FSSAI Licenses\n\n| Type | Turnover | Cost | Validity |\n|------|---------|------|----------|\n| Basic Registration | <₹12 Lakh/year | ₹100 | 1-5 years |\n| State License | ₹12L-20 Cr | ₹2,000-5,000 | 1-5 years |\n| Central License | >₹20 Cr OR exporter | ₹7,500 | 1-5 years |\n\n**For export**: Always apply for **Central License** regardless of turnover.\n\n### Documents Required\n1. Form B (application form)\n2. PAN card\n3. GST certificate\n4. Proof of possession of business premises\n5. Food safety management plan (HACCP)\n6. Water test report\n7. NOC from local body (Panchayat/Municipality)\n8. Blueprint/plan of processing area\n9. List of equipment with capacity\n10. List of products with HS codes\n\n### Application Process\n1. Register at **foscos.fssai.gov.in**\n2. Fill Form B (online)\n3. Upload all documents\n4. Pay fee online\n5. Inspector visit within 30 days\n6. License issued in 30-60 days\n\n### Common Rejection Reasons\n- Incomplete HACCP plan\n- Missing water test report\n- Blueprint not matching specifications\n- Missing NOC from local body\n- Incorrect product category selection\n\n### FSSAI and Export\n- Your FSSAI number must appear on all export labels\n- Export Inspection Agency (EIA) works with FSSAI for compliance\n- Annual audit required for continued compliance\n\n## Key Contact\n**FSSAI Helpdesk**: 1800-11-4406 (Toll Free)\n**Website**: fssai.gov.in\n\n*Reach out to Avani Agro Foods for sourcing from FSSAI-licensed manufacturers.*`
